# Weavo

When the user mentions **Weavo** or **weavo**, treat it as this project unless they clearly mean something else.

- **GitHub**: https://github.com/Anurag810/weavo
- **Local workspace**: `/Users/anuragmishra/MindLoop/weavo`
- **Author**: Anurag810 (Anurag Mishra)

## What it is

Full-stack dynamic UI framework: SCSS theming (CSS variables/tokens), React component library, JSON schema renderer, Rust/WASM `.wv` parser (`weavo-compiler`), Express backend, Ollama AI integration, and a planned drag-and-drop builder.

## Stack

- React 19 + Vite + SCSS
- CLI: `bin/weavo.js` (`dev`, `build`, `setup-requirements`)
- Rust/WASM: `Cargo.toml` → `weavo-compiler`
- Backend: `src/server.js` (Express)

## Key paths

- `src/scss-core/` — theme tokens and styles
- `src/components/` — React UI + layout components (19 total)
- `src/schema-renderer/` — JSON → React renderer
- `src/builder/mock-schemas/` — sample `.wv` / JSON schemas

